mplicates direct access since it’s abstract. I wonder if I can utilize the concrete subclass DTDParser.Catalog instead. However, its class loader seems to be non-null. I also need to assess whether line 506 could interact with native images, as Class.getClassLoader() for application classes might return null or be irrelevant. I’m curious about how JacoCo works with the JVM and if dynamic-access reports can provide insights based on the native agent during execution.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_NuIodwLq4SodRsa0uNusgHRz|fc_02027b253bf081e90169f76abb5a6c81a3a530274a21af5d3b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find metadata/com.sun.xml.dtd-parser/dtd-parser -type f -maxdepth 5 -print -exec sed -n '1,120p' {} \\;"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4453, "output": 823, "cacheRead": 14848, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20124, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777822382995, "responseId": "resp_02027b253bf081e90169f76aaf61ec81a38928d9d29ea1978e"}}
